  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed rear dormer, by reason of its scale, size and detailed design, would result in an incompatible form of development, which would adversely affect the character and appearance of the host building, the wider terrace within which it is located and the historic and architectural interest of the Victoria Park Conservation Area. As such, the proposal is considered contrary to the policies D1 (London’s form, character and capacity for growth), D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach), D4 (Delivering good design) and HC1 (Heritage Conservation and growth) of the London Plan (2021) and Policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP4 (Non Designated Heritage Assets) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and the relevant sections Hackney’s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
